    "main_causes": [
      "GGUF UD-Q4_K_M starts from a larger mixed-quant payload than PARO w4_paro: local files are ~20.61 GiB GGUF vs ~19.24 GiB PARO safetensors.",
      "GGUF decode-repack keeps T16 decode-friendly layouts resident for many tensors (including selected experts and Q8 dense layers); this is speed-oriented but leaves less VRAM headroom than PARO's native packed layout.",
      "GGUF resident session keeps monolithic prefill hidden buffers and chunk-sized bulk scratch resident for the whole session; PARO allocates/frees more prefill workspace transiently, so tracked peak can be higher than current but steady-state is lower.",
      "Both models have the same 10 full-attention layers and BF16 KV-cache slope, but GGUF has a higher base footprint, so it reaches the 24 GiB ceiling around ~35K context while PARO still fits 128K with conservative chunks.",
      "There is at least one low-hanging GGUF memory cleanup: _GGUFFullAttentionPrefillScratch still allocates one-layer key_cache/value_cache buffers even though full-attention prefill replaces them with the resident KV cache; that costs ~64 MiB at 32K and ~256 MiB at 128K, helpful but not enough alone."
    ]
  },
